3. **Inspect Wiring Connections**: Carefully examine all wiring connections within the affected area. Look for loose wires, damaged insulation, or signs of overheating. Tighten any loose connections and repair or replace any damaged components. Ensure that all connections are secure and properly insulated to prevent short circuits.

