In addition to producing off-flavors, Dekkera strains have also been implicated in spoilage events due to their production of acetic acid and other undesirable metabolites. As such, winemakers and brewers must carefully monitor levels of this microorganism during fermentation processes if they wish to avoid potential issues related to contamination by Dekkera spp..

